\cf0 That's the entire current MCP sample. The H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f0  uncertainty isn't dominated by maser modeling at this point \'97 it's dominated by 
\f1\b peculiar velocity corrections
\f0\b0  for a sample of only 6 galaxies. Each galaxy has a recession velocity uncertainty of ~250 km/s due to local flows, which at ~5000\'9610,000 km/s recession velocities translates to a few-percent per-galaxy H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f0  error. With 6 galaxies, you get ~4% precision on the mean \'97 the famous \'b13.0 km/s/Mpc.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 The tension with the rest of the field\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f0\b0\fs24 \cf0 Here's where masers earn their special status in the H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f0  debate:\
The MCP value of 
\f1\b 73.9 \'b1 3.0
\f0\b0  is consistent with SH0ES (73.04), MCP (itself), Pop-II (73.8), Mira (73.3), and adh0cc (~75) \'97 and discrepant with Planck (67.4) at the ~2\uc0\u963  level. Because masers share 
\f1\b zero rungs
\f0\b0  with any of the SN Ia ladders, this consistency cannot be explained away by Cepheid systematics, TRGB systematics, dust corrections, crowding bias, peculiar velocities of SN Ia hosts, host-environment standardization, or any of the other "hidden systematic in the ladder" arguments that come up periodically in the literature.\
The escape routes from a high MCP value are essentially:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Wrong disk geometry assumption.
\f0\b0  If the disks aren't pure Keplerian (warps, eccentricity, deviation from edge-on) the inferred distance is biased. NGC 4258 has been studied to death and shows a small but real warp; the model accounts for it. Other disks are less well-characterized.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Peculiar velocity systematics.
\f0\b0  With 6 galaxies the field is undersampled. Different bulk-flow models (2M++, CosmicFlows-3 reconstruction, no correction) shift H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f0  by ~2 km/s/Mpc. Pesce+20 reports H
\f2 \uc0\u8320 
\f0  values ranging from 71.8 to 76.9 across PV treatments \'97 a meaningful chunk of the headline error bar.\
\ls3\ilvl0
\f1\b \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Black hole mass priors.
\f0\b0  Tight, but propagated.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 None of these can plausibly bring MCP down to Planck values.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

